args: ...Desires and Jails are still strange to me,\nbut I think I've got a handle on the basics.
Don't sweat it; there's still a lot about\nthem that even we don't fully understand.
But that's all the information\nwe have at the moment.
The rest will have to be hands-on training.
Just talking about fighting Shadows\ninside a Jail isn't enough.
You have to actually do itâ€”\nand we're gonna show you how!
Nice! So do we all charge in together\nright now or what?
Are you nuts? They'd be all over us\nin no time if we did that!
A Phantom Thief melts into the shadows\nbefore erupting on the scene with style\nand stealing the Treasure!
And THAT'S what we're gonna teach you\nhow to do. Now c'mon!
Okay, here's how we're splitting up:
Sophie and Cleo, you're a team.
I hope I can assist you, Cleo.
Panther and Elisanne, you're team two.
Er, yes. Let us proceed in...rocking\nwith all due haste.
Team three is me and Luca.
Just do what I say and you'll be fine.
Mold me like a clay pot, cat!
In that case, your first lesson is that\nI am NOT a cat! The things I deal with...
I guess that puts me with Joker, then.
All right, team up with your battle buddy\nand let's get to training.
Each group is to take out 30 Shadows\nand then meet up back here. Oh,\nand remember the cardinal rule:
Do it like a phantom thief.
You got it, Joker. Now let's go!
Oh, I guess I was just worrying about\neveryoneâ€”I tend to do that a lot.
For now, let's just trust them.
...Whew! It was a fearsome battle,\nbut we saw it through.
Likewise, Pantherâ€”though I must say,\nfighting in an unfamiliar way certainly\nuses a lot of energy.

Still, if I understand all of this, the way of
a phantom thief is to survey a situation
from the high ground before unleashing
a surprise attack on the enemy.
That's it, all right! Pretty cool, huh?

It is ï¼‚coolï¼‚ for certain, although it goes
against much of my training as a Paladyn,
where we are taught to meet an enemy
face-to-face in honorable combat.
I am merely having a difficult time\ngrasping Sophie's lessons.

Why? You just find the enemy and then
give them a wham. Then you follow up
with a big kablam and get out of there
with a zoooom.
That sounds...rough. I wonder how\nHis Highness and Luca are faring?
Quit yappin' away like you're some\nkinda feline genius, kitty cat!
How many times do I have to tell you,\nbunny boy? I am NOT a cat!
Uh oh. What's everyone arguing about?
There's too much tension in the air.\nWe're not coming together as a team.
My assessment is that it would be quite\ndangerous to go to the Jail in this state.
Well, we've all only just met each other;\nit's not much of a surprise that we're not\ncooperating as well as we could yet.
I think we just need to get to know\neach other a little bit better.
Watch and learn, cat! I'll show you how\nLuca does thingsâ€”and it ain't by sneakin'\naround in the dark like some kinda thief!
Get your own tongue, cat! Yaaaah!
You're right. He and the Monarch already\nknow each other, plus he's not exactly\nused to how Jails work yet.
Er, okay. Let's split up into two groups.\nOne group will bait the Shadows, and the\nother will grab Luca and get out of here.
Me, Panther, and Sophie will be the bait.\nJoker, you lead everyone to the castle.
There's no time to be indecisive.
Don't worry, Jokerâ€”I believe in you.
Hey, what do you think you're doing?!
We have to fall back, Luca!
They're giving you a chance.\nDon't throw it away.
The security level's gone up again.\nWe have to leaveâ€”now.
Er, and sorry about that. I was getting\nannoyed how slow everything was going,\nand I just kinda...snapped.
Your friends must be in real trouble\nby now, Joker. I'm very sorry.
I'm going back to help them out.\nMind lending a hand?
Like a phantom thief, of course.\nHere's the plan...
Do you truly think that will work?
It's too dangerous to go by yourself,\nJoker. There must be another way.
(His desire to save his friends is so strong.\nI can feel it emanating from him.)
(If anyone can do this, he can.)
All right. We'll do it your way.
Can I count on the rest of you?
